Mint Mobile Cookie Policy
California residents have the right to opt out of the "sale" or “share” of their personal information. Under California law, “sale” is defined broadly to include the sharing of personal information in exchange for anything of value, which isn’t limited to the exchange of money. “Share” is targeted advertising, defined narrowly as providing personal information to a third party for cross-context behavioral advertising to a consumer based on information about their activity on multiple websites across the internet. For more details on sale and share, see “Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information explained” in the Mint Mobile Privacy Policy.
To opt out of sale or share activities which rely on cookies or other similar online tracking technologies, please select your preferences using the toggle below.
If you are a current customer and do not want to receive marketing emails, you can opt-out by logging into your account and setting your email preferences.
The actions to block or decline sale or share cookies or other similar online tracking technologies are specific to the browser or device you are using at the time of your selection. If you clear your cookies, browse in incognito mode, use a different web browser or access our website using a different device, you will need to opt out again.
For more on our privacy practices, and other choices or rights that may be available to you, please see the
Privacy Policy.
Always Active
These cookies are necessary for our website to provide the service, application, or resource requested and cannot be switched off in our systems. You can, however, set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but some parts of the site then may not function as expected or in a secure way. These cookies do not store any personally identifiable information.
Targeting Cookies
These cookies may be set through our site by our advertising partners. They may be used by those companies to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites. They do not store directly personal information, but are based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device. You may choose to turn off targeted advertising with the toggle switch here . For clarity, targeting advertising cookies are turned off when you switch the toggle to the left, turning it to grey, and confirm your choice.
